<br>
Fear kiting in the Grey with a rogue got me through 2 orange of 59 in a couple days.  with a monk or a warrior, around the same.<br>
<br>
snare song + fear song + regen/stacking haste (epic proc for basic haste).  fear song and charm takes care of most adds.<br>
<br>
Druid + bard on root rotting also = pretty damn fast mob deaths.  (bard dots become 33% more effective when the mob is rooted, for one)<br>
<br>
wizard + bard...well, generally I just try and keep aggro and dots on a single mob and run it around while the wizard nukes.  Anarligen is trying to get me to learn how to quad with him...but since bard ae songs are basically all pbae, hasn't exactly been a success.<br>
<br>
and places like fungus grove...well, throw just about any 2 classes together there and they'll duo well.<br>
<br>
~Kat (wants to learn how to duo/solo summoning mobs...darn druids and shamans!) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucerosofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 570<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 4:44:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2369.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: rogue solo</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> (bard dots become 33% more effective when the mob is rooted, for one)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->All dots work like this.  If the dotted mob is chasing you, they do 66% of their damage.  If the monster is stationary or running away, the dot does full damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukatarinandolini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katarin Andolini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 183<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 4:51:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2369.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.smilies-world.de/Smilies/Smilies_klein/Smilies_klein_1/booaa.gif height=40 width=40></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: rogue solo</span><hr size=1> I know that.  I was stating it because most classes with dots HAVE root, so it's not a constant problem for them.  People sometimes see bards kiting down a mob and taking forever, and assume bard dots do nil damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> 